<H3> <TI>   Cavaco Silva Comments on East Timor Situation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302121594 Lisbon Radio Renascenca in Portuguese to Europe 
1130 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon Radio Renascenca </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Cavaco Silva reacted to a documentary 
on East Timor denouncing a second massacre by Indonesian troops. 
The prime minister was speaking at a news conference under way 
at Sao Bento. Cavaco Silva is giving a joint news conference 
with his Israeli counterpart. Raquel Abecassis reports: 
  [Abecassis] This was the first question Cavaco Silva had to 
answer. He spoke without any problem about the documentary 
shown on television on the second massacre in East Timor: 
  [Begin Cavaco recording] Once again we receive shocking 
images of Indonesia's behavior in Timor. We hope that these 
images will help the international community to be even more 
aware of the need to pressure the Indonesian Government as much 
as possible to respect human rights in the territory. I can 
also say that we were already working with information very 
similar to that revealed yesterday, information we have received 
from the resistance [words indistinct]. [end recording] 

