<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Finance, Deputy Ministers Appointed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2402142394 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1230 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2402142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Finance Minister Alexandros Papadhopoulos 
and Nikolaos Kiriazidhis, an expert at the Finance Ministry, 
will be sworn in as finance minister and deputy finance minister 
respectively. The swearing-in ceremony will be held at noon 
tomorrow before President Konstandinos Karamanlis and Prime 
Minister Andreas Papandreou. 
  Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said that the 
changes in the Finance Ministry were made following 
consultations between Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou and 
National Economy Minister Yeoryios Yennimatas. 

</TEXT>

