<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll: 53 Percent Favor of EU Membership </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2502145294 Vienna KURIER in German 25 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2502145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna KURIER </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Before Final Round: Still Bare </F>
Majority for Entry Into European Union"] 
  [Text] The latest opinion poll of the Integral Institute 
carried out on behalf of KURIER, indicates a bare, but clear 
agreement of the Austrians to the European Union [EU]. In a 
referendum, about 53 percent would currently decide in favor of 
Brussels. With 58 percent, men are even more prepared to say 
yes to Europe, women are more skeptical. The Austrians regard 
the field of agriculture and the farmers as the biggest problem 
in the EU negotiations. 

</TEXT>

