<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Simulator Delivered to Russian Nuclear Station </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2502104794 Helsinki KAUPPALEHTI in Finnish 8 Feb 94 p 9 </F>
<F P=103> BR2502104794 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki KAUPPALEHTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "IVO Delivers Simulator to Kola Power </F>
Station"] 
  [Text] IVO, a subsidiary of the Imatran Voima company, is 
to deliver a simulator to Russia's Kola Nuclear Power Station 
for technical failure and emergency management training. The 
simulator will improve the ability of the operators to control 
the power station in case of a breakdown or an accident. The 
simulator can also be used to test the effects of the plans to 
transform the plant's operations. 
  The delivery, worth about 1 million Finnish markkas, is 
financed by the Commerce and Industry Ministry and the Foreign 
Ministry. The delivery has been made within the framework of 
the safety improvement program for nuclear power stations in 
Russia. The simulator, which will be shipped to Kola in April, 
is scheduled to be operational in September. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

